        <p class="metadata">Posted by Darby Felton (darby) on 2007-03-09T07:48:38.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>As previously mentioned, no matter what the classes are named, people are going to have to read documentation. Having a class name of Validator may seem more sensible than Validate to some folks, and to others it would likely make less sense. Regardless, it is an immaterial change when compared with the impact of changing a class name in core.</p>

<p>Class names were discussed during the proposal period for this component, and I also voted for the Validator name. But I and others having this opinion were overruled, and Validate was the chosen name for this component. (Originally I had chosen the name Valid, since it's shorter :))</p>

<p>If there were other backward-incompatible API changes pending on the component, we would have an opportunity to change the name along with making the other API changes. But as it stands currently, we would just be changing the name for the sake of changing the name, and the cost is not worth the value at this late hour, when we are wrapping up incomplete items for 0.9.0.</p>

